The Master's seminar of literature and theatre studies takes place in the 1st term and in two specialized groups: Estonian literature and world literature. Part of the seminars are common to all participants. At the seminar the students get acquainted with the demands set for the thesis, analyze earlier master's theses, read scholarly articles of their field, learn to use  archive materials, etc. In the end of the seminar the student presents a preliminary plan for the Master's thesis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the Master's seminar is to support the writing of the Master's thesis and to offer both the specialized and the interdisciplinary forum for discussion.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The seminar directs the student to work systematically with his/her Master's thesis, to plan and organize it, to learn to ask research questions and to choose theoretical/methodological approach and the volume of the work according to them. The supervisor of the thesis takes also part in the work of the seminar.
